Possible sources for independent study research

"A Primer for Program Composition Notation" Chandy, K. Mani and Taylor, Stephen (1990). A Primer for Program Composition Notation. California Institute of Technology.  http://resolver.caltech.edu/CaltechCSTR:1990.cs-tr-90-10



"Recursive and Dynamic Software Composition with Sharing". E. Bruneton, T. Coupaye, and J. B. Stefani. France Télécom R&D. http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.19.4559&rep=rep1&type=pdf
composition dimension: for structure of models composed (p. 1)
dynamism dimension: for composition of dynamically changing attributes (p. 1)
Requirements for composition of component-based systems: encapsulation and identity, composition, sharing, life-cycle, activities, control, mobility. (p. 1-3)
Fractal component: has a controller and content.  The content may include other components. (p. 3)


"The Design of a Resource-Aware Reflective Middleware Architecture". Gordon S. Blair, Fábio Costa, Geoff Coulson, Fabien Delpiano, Hector Duran, Bruno Dumant, François Horn, Nikos Parlavantzas, Jean-Bernard Stefani. Computing Department, Lancaster University, Bailrigg, Lancaster LA1 4YR, UK. https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Fabio_Costa4/publication/221448298_The_Design_of_a_Resource-Aware_Reflective_Middleware_Architecture/links/0912f50b7b39539646000000.pdf.


"Middleware: a model for distributed system services." Philip A. Bernstein. Communications of the ACM, Vol. 39 Issue 2, Feb 1996. http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=230809. http://delivery.acm.org/10.1145/240000/230809/p86-bernstein.pdf?ip=149.169.122.228&id=230809&acc=ACTIVE%20SERVICE&key=B63ACEF81C6334F5.BD7B0059B564CDBA.4D4702B0C3E38B35.4D4702B0C3E38B35&CFID=651279953&CFTOKEN=60278623&__acm__=1470175317_5f405779294865161766fbe2b2a07c2f


"Mandated Requirements for Hardware/Software Combination in Safety-Critical Systems." Adrian J. Hilton and Jon G. Hall.  2003.  http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.523.8938&rep=rep1&type=pdf
The effects of standards on combined systems is analyzed in the context of programmable logic devices.



Algorithm Design. Jon Kleinberg and Eva Tardos. Pearson Education, 2006.
Composable Cellular Automata. Gary R. Mayer and Hessam S. Sarjoughian. Arizona State University. Simulation Transactions, 85(11-12), 735-749, 2009.
Pygrass: An Object Oriented Python Application Programming Interface (API) for Geographic Resources Analysis Support System (GRASS) Geographic Information System (GIS). Pietro Zambelli, Sören Gebbert, and Marco Ciolli. ISPRS International Journal of Geo-Information, 2(1), 201-219, 2013.
Software Complexity Measurement. Kearney, Sedlmeyer, Thompson, Gray, and Adler. Communications of the ACM, 29(11), 1044-1050, 1986.




"Multi-scale analysis of a household level agent-based model of landcover change." Tom P. Evans and Hugh Kelley. http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0301479704000787
Examines the scalability of an agent-based landscape simulation.


"Agent-based modeling: Methods and techniques for simulating human systems." Eric Bonabeau. http://www.pnas.org/content/99/suppl_3/7280.full
Introduces ABM in the context of business applications.
